   <string>
When a cleric needs to keep track of comrades that may get
separated, status allows him to mentally monitor their relative
position and general condition. The cleric is aware of direction
and distance to the creatures and their status: unharmed,
wounded, disabled, staggered, unconscious, dying, dead, etc. Once
the spell has been cast upon the subjects, the distance between
them and the caster does not affect the spell as long as they are
on the same plane of existence. If they leave it, the spell
ceases to function for them.
